Security architecture diagram: Three defense layers for RAG. LAYER 1 (Input): Document Upload -> Security Scanner (regex patterns) -> Block/Allow -> Indexing. LAYER 2 (Storage): PostgreSQL with Row Level Security (RLS) policy visualization - Tenant A sees only Tenant A data. LAYER 3 (Output): LLM Response -> Output Filter (forbidden patterns) -> Safe Response / Blocked. Shield icons, red/green indicators, technical style.